Description: Tools to fit a boundary line model (Webb, 1972) to a data set and 
    make statistical inferences about its parameters. It tests a data set for 
    evidence of boundary presence, fit a boundary line model and conduct post-hoc 
    analysis e.g. prediction of boundary values and the most limiting factor.
    See Miti et al. (2024)<doi.org/10.1016/j.fcr.2024.109365>.
